UAL Inc's United Airlines said it willoffer scheduled service between Burbank, Calif., and Denver,Colo., starting June five.    United said it will operate two daily round-trip flights inthe Burbank to Denver market using new Boeing Co &lt;BA> 737-300aircraft.    United said as a promotion for its new route it will offera bonus of double mileage to all members of its frequent flyerprgram, Mileage Plus, who fly the Burbank-Denver route duringthe first 45 days of service. Reuter&#3;